            "created_at": "1775751222",
            "text": "Couple in Indonesia Caned for Premarital Relations Under Sharia Law\n\nBanda Aceh, Indonesia: A couple in Indonesia’s Aceh province was publicly caned after being found guilty of engaging in premarital relations, authorities confirmed. Each received 100 lashes as part of the punishment carried out under the region’s strict implementation of Islamic Sharia law.\n\nThe punishment took place in front of a crowd, with officials and onlookers present as the sentence was executed. Aceh is the only province in Indonesia that enforces Sharia law, where offenses such as gambling, alcohol consumption, and consensual relations outside marriage are punishable by caning.\n\nLocal authorities stated that the punishment was conducted in accordance with existing regulations. The individuals were reportedly detained earlier after being accused of violating local moral laws.\n\nHuman rights organizations have repeatedly criticized such punishments, calling them harsh and in violation of international human rights standards. However, local officials continue to defend the practice, citing cultural and religious values upheld in the province.\n\nThe incident has once again sparked debate globally over the use of corporal punishment and the enforcement of moral laws in certain regions.",
